---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words with Prefix FORE in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Strategy Guide"
  description="Master FORE prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include FORECAST, FOREHEAD, FOREIGN, FOREVER, FORESIGHT. 4-tile prefix worth 7 points — F(4) gives high base."
  keywords="words with prefix fore scrabble, fore words scrabble, forecast scrabble, fore prefix strategy, forehead scrabble points, scrabble words starting with fore"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Words with Prefix FORE in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Strategy Guide", "description": "Master FORE prefix words in Scrabble. 4-tile prefix worth 7 points with F(4) providing high base value. Top plays include FORECAST, FOREHEAD, FOREIGN, FOREVER.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-prefix-fore" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best FORE prefix words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top FORE words include FORESIGHT (16pts), FOREHEAD (15pts), FORECAST (13pts), and FOREVER (13pts). The F(4) tile in the prefix gives these words a strong scoring base. FORESIGHT combines the prefix with GH(6) for a powerful bingo candidate." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is the FORE prefix worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "FORE is worth 7 points (F=4, O=1, R=1, E=1). The F tile alone contributes more than half the prefix value at 4 points. This makes FORE one of the higher-scoring 4-tile prefixes, on par with MEGA (7pts) and above SEMI (6pts) or MINI (6pts)." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can FORE words score bingos in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — FORE is 4 tiles, so you need 3 more for a 7-letter bingo. FOREIGN (7 letters, 11pts + 50 bonus = 61pts) is the cleanest example. FORECAST (8 letters) and FOREHEAD (8 letters) also hit bingo with style. The F tile ensures even modest bingos score well." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Prefix Guides</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words with Prefix FORE in Scrabble</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">FORE means "before" or "in front" — and on the Scrabble board, it puts you ahead of your opponent. F(4) alone provides more than half the prefix value, giving every FORE word a built-in scoring advantage. With dozens of common English words starting with FORE (forecast, forehead, forever), this is one of the most recognizable prefixes you'll encounter on your rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles to Bingo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top FORE Words by Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">FORESIGHT — 16 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 letters. Ability to predict. G(2)+H(4) adds 6 points to the extension.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">FOREHEAD — 15 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. Part of the face. H(4)+D(2) make a strong 8-letter bingo target.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">FORECAST — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. Weather prediction. C(3) extends well. Everyday vocabulary.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">FOREVER — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 letters. Eternity. V(4) adds punch. Exactly 7 tiles = bingo-eligible.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More FORE Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOREIGN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOREARM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOREMAN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOREWORD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The F-Tile Advantage</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">F is worth <span class="text-white font-medium">4 points</span> — placing it in a prefix means every FORE word starts with a scoring head start. Unlike ULTRA (all 1-pointers), FORE frontloads value. On a Double Letter square, F alone contributes 8 points. That single tile can make or break whether FORE outscores other plays on your rack.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">FORE Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FOREVER is a natural 7:</span> F-O-R-E-V-E-R uses exactly 7 tiles. With V(4) in the extension, that's 13 + 50 = 63 points. Watch for this pattern on your rack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rich extension vocabulary:</span> FORE has more valid extensions than most prefixes — forecast, forehead, foreign, forearm, foreman, foreword, foresee, foresight. You'll recognize these without memorization.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">F on premium squares:</span> If you can place F on a Triple Letter (12pts from one tile) or Double Word (doubles the F contribution), FORE words become explosive scorers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FORE through board E:</span> If E exists on the board, you can extend through it — playing just F-O-R plus your extension tiles. This saves tiles and still gives full scoring credit.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">FORE Scoring Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">F</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">4 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">O</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">R</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">E</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">=</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">7</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">total</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-back/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Starting with BACK: Opposite Direction Prefix</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-auto/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix AUTO: Self-Governing Scrabble Plays</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all FORE words instantly — enter your tiles and see every valid play</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
